  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Morbidly obese subjects with a BMI &gt;40 kg/m2 who are eligible for bariatric surgery
             and have accepted to undergo RYGB

          -  Weight stable for at least 6 months before the study (+/- 5 kg within the previous 6
             months)

          -  Stable medication

          -  Provision of informed consent

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients not eligible for laparoscopic RYGB

          -  Incapacity to give a valid informed consent or unwilling to give the consent

          -  Pregnancy or lactating

          -  Type 2-diabetes mellitus

          -  Significant illness within the two weeks preceding surgery, as judged by the
             physician.

          -  Obvious infection (bacteria, virus etc)

          -  Major cardiovascular disease

          -  Major gastrointestinal, respiratory, or any hormonal disorders

          -  History of drug addiction and/or alcohol use

          -  Suspected or confirmed poor compliance

          -  Alcohol consumption of &gt; 20 g per day in the case of women and &gt; 30 g per day in the
             case of men for at least 3 consecutive months during the previous 5 years

          -  Presence of hepatitis C or frank cirrhosis.
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
